sentences: Tom Middleton (born 18 August 1971) is a British electronic recording artist, sound designer, composer, music producer, remixer and DJ.
His solo albums include Lifetracks (2007), Glasstracks (2011) and Sleep Better (2018).

A classically trained pianist and cellist, Middleton worked in the early 1990s with Richard D. James (with whom he shares the same birthdate), co-producing "En-Trance to Exit" on the Analogue Bubblebath EP for Mighty Force Records.
Global Communication's 1994 ambient album 76:14 is considered to be a landmark of the genre.
A compilation of early Evolution material was released jointly by Evolution and Warp Records in 1995 as The Theory of Evolution.
In 2007, Middleton abandoned the AMBA moniker, while still focusing on the ambient genre fusing classical traditions with electronica, featuring orchestral, choral and electro acoustic arrangements.
A new EP, Excursions 1 was released in September 2007 while the album Lifetracks was released on Big Chill Recordings in October 2007 under the name Tom Middleton.
